---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Metrics & Questions" section="metrics">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">18 · Measure & Validate</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Leading indicators, <em>lagging outcomes.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Two-bucket ROI discipline. Performance spend defends with payback math. Foundational spend defends with strategic outcome metrics. Both accountable — different questions.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>Two buckets, two defenses: performance spend defends with payback math, foundational spend defends with strategic outcomes. Both are accountable — just to different questions. Never let foundational get judged on CAC.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="metrics"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Progress: <span data-progress-here="metrics">0 / 0</span></p>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Leading indicators</h3>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.75rem">90-Day Visibility</p>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>MQL volume + quality (volume growth with maintained qualification)</li>
        <li>Pipeline sourced by marketing (by segment: solo / group / DSO)</li>
        <li>Email engagement (opens, clicks, replies, conversions by lifecycle stage)</li>
        <li>SEO performance (rankings, organic traffic, branded search volume)</li>
        <li>AEO presence (citations in AI assistant answers — Otterly/Profound tracked)</li>
        <li>Content velocity (case studies, posts, webinars — AI workflow throughput)</li>
        <li>Sales enablement asset usage (battle card invocations, content downloads by AE)</li>
        <li>Customer engagement (member email, lifecycle program performance)</li>
        <li>Practice directory traffic + conversion to enrollment (when launched)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Lagging indicators</h3>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:0.75rem">12-Month Outcomes</p>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
        <li>New logo revenue (ARR from net new practices/DSOs) — Bucket 01</li>
        <li>Expansion revenue (member growth at existing practices) — Bucket 02</li>
        <li>Retention (practice + member retention rates) — Bucket 03</li>
        <li>CAC by segment and channel</li>
        <li>LTV by practice tier and segment</li>
        <li>Net Revenue Retention (PE-favorite, Charlesbank reporting metric)</li>
        <li>Brand authority (share of voice, branded search, AEO citation rate)</li>
        <li>Category leadership (Becker's / GDN / Hint-comparable industry presence)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>ROI discipline — <em>two buckets.</em></h2>
  <div class="callout">
    <div class="lbl">Performance Spend</div>
    <p><strong>Paid search, paid social, syndication, trade shows.</strong> Defends with payback math. If a channel can't hit defined ROI hurdles in 90 days, it gets cut. No emotional attachment.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <div class="lbl">Foundational Spend</div>
    <p><strong>SEO, content, website, tech stack, lifecycle infrastructure.</strong> Defends with strategic outcome metrics — share of voice, organic traffic growth, brand search volume, NRR. Compounds over time. Don't kill quarterly.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>12 open questions — <em>validate during onboarding.</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft)">Confirm during first 30 days before committing to specific bets.</p>

  <div data-section="metrics">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-01-team" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q1 · Current marketing team composition, capabilities, gaps</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-02-charlesbank" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q2 · Charlesbank specific growth targets, NRR expectations, fundraise/exit horizon</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-03-payment" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q3 · Payment plan partnership details — Sunbit vs others, terms, timing</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-04-cust-infra" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q4 · Customer marketing infrastructure — what's wired vs unwired in Pardot</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-05-bridge" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q5 · Bridge adoption rate across customer base, attach rate to new logo deals</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-06-sales" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q6 · Sales team structure, SDR motion, ICP definition, pipeline coverage</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-07-partners" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q7 · Existing partner relationships beyond payment plan</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-08-data" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q8 · Customer data infrastructure quality + attribution capability</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-09-compliance" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q9 · Compliance constraints — DMPO, Knox-Keene, state-specific for consumer-facing</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-10-content" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q10 · Existing content library and brand assets</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-11-budget" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q11 · Budget envelope for first year, expected ramp, conference separate or bundled</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="q-12-relationships" data-section="metrics" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Q12 · Existing analyst, PR, agency relationships</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">CEO 1:1 — answers to open questions <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="metrics-jim-answers" placeholder="Q1: ...&#10;Q2: ...&#10;Q3: ...&#10;Q4: ...&#10;Capture answers as you validate each question..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="callout mint">
    <div class="lbl">Hub Complete</div>
    <p>You've reached the end of the strategy hub. <strong>Export to markdown</strong> from the sidebar to share progress with your team. All notes, statuses, and checkboxes are saved to your browser locally — they persist until you reset or clear browser data.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/90day"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">17 · First 90 Days</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri"><span class="dir">↑ Top</span><span class="name">00 · Dashboard</span></a>
  </div>

</div>
</ClerriLayout>
